  "texts": [
    "(27) While news media does not drastically change or alter an individuals perception of a given topic, it does determine an individuals perception about public opinion and social climate, thereby influencing popular opinion in a more subtle, indirect way.",
    "Research in the field v of media studies has delved into the dynamics of how media content influences audience perceptions.",
    "To tackle the inherent challenges psychology faces in analyzing media content, a new approach called Media Framing Analysis has been introduced.",
    "This method aims to provide deeper insights into the ways media narratives shape public opinion and discourse.",
    "Additionally, studies on the topic of news media trust have examined its effect on individual media consumption habits, especially in contexts where consumers are presented with a multitude of media choices."
  ]
}